---
import LayoutFunnel from '@/layouts/LayoutFunnel.astro';
---

<LayoutFunnel title="B2B Tech Revenue Architecture | Marketing by Besic">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl text-center">
      <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-brand/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-8">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-brand" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z" />
        </svg>
      </div>

      <h1 class="heading-xl mb-6">
        Your Sales Team Wastes 80% of Their Time on Leads Who Will Never Buy. We Fix That.
      </h1>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        Your pipeline is full. Your close rate is anemic. The problem isn't your sales team -- it's the qualification architecture feeding them unqualified leads.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Image (placeholder: using luxury image until b2b-specific asset available) -->
      <img src="/offer-luxury-hero.webp" alt="B2B Tech Revenue Architecture (placeholder image)" class="w-full rounded-lg mb-12 object-cover max-h-[500px]" width="1200" height="500" loading="eager" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Three Reasons Your Pipeline Is Full but Your Revenue Is Flat</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 1: High Lead Volume, Low Conversion</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            Your CRM shows 500 leads this quarter. Your closed deals show 12. That's a 2.4% close rate, which means 97.6% of your sales team's time is burned on leads who were never going to buy. The problem isn't follow-up -- it's that your marketing attracts the wrong people.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 2: Generic Marketing Language Attracts Tire-Kickers</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            "We help businesses grow with innovative solutions." That copy attracts everyone, which means it qualifies no one. Decision-makers with budget authority don't respond to generic value propositions. They respond to specific problem descriptions that prove you understand their exact situation. Your marketing is casting a wide net and catching the wrong fish.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 3: No Revenue Attribution</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            You can't tell which campaigns drive actual signed contracts. Your marketing reports say "generated 150 MQLs." Your CFO asks "which of those became revenue?" Silence. Without closed-loop attribution from first touch to signed contract, you're optimizing for activity, not outcomes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Image (placeholder: using luxury image) -->
      <img src="/offer-luxury-problem.webp" alt="B2B pipeline leak diagnosis (placeholder image)" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">The Intent-Driven Revenue Architecture</h2>

      <!-- Phase 1 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 1: Sales Mechanism Audit</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              We map your pipeline from first touch to signed contract and identify the qualification gap. Where do deals die? Which lead sources produce revenue and which produce noise? You'll see exactly where your sales mechanism is leaking -- not opinions, forensic data.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 2 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 2: Intent-Driven Friction Architecture</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              We add psychological qualification filters that repel low-intent leads and attract buyers. Counterintuitive but proven: making it harder to contact your sales team increases close rates. Application forms. Qualification questions. Friction that filters for budget authority and genuine need -- not curiosity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 3 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 3: Closed-Loop Revenue System</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Connect every marketing euro to every signed contract. CRM integration that traces attribution from first ad click through discovery call through proposal through closed deal. Your CFO finally gets the answer to "which campaigns make us money?" and your marketing team finally gets the data to double down on what works.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution Image (placeholder: using luxury image) -->
      <img src="/offer-luxury-solution.webp" alt="Intent-Driven Revenue Architecture system (placeholder image)" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution Gap Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#111111] relative z-10">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Most Agencies Deliver Reports. We Deliver Revenue.</h2>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center">
        The gap between knowing your pipeline is leaking and actually fixing the qualification architecture is where B2B companies waste years and millions. Your last marketing hire "improved brand awareness." Your close rate didn't move. Our framework closes the execution gap by rebuilding the mechanism, not the marketing.
      </p>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center font-semibold text-brand">
        We restructured a tech consultancy's sales mechanism and delivered 412% ROI by adding one counterintuitive step: we made it harder to contact their sales team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 pb-48">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-6">Apply for a Revenue Diagnosis</h2>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        We work with B2B tech companies and SaaS businesses generating EUR 2M+ annually with sales teams that close less than 10% of qualified pipeline. If your pipeline is full but your revenue is flat, apply below.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center w-full">
        <a
          href="/en/apply"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold text-white transition-all duration-300 bg-[#8224e3] rounded-lg hover:bg-[#6a1ca6] hover:scale-105 shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(130,36,227,0.4)]"
        >
          Apply for Revenue Diagnosis
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LayoutFunnel>
